ca.cgjennings.ui

Class JWebPanel

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container
        • javax.swing.JComponent
          • javax.swing.JPanel
            • ca.cgjennings.ui.JWebPanel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ImageObserver, MenuContainer, Serializable, Accessible

    public class JWebPanel
extends JPanel
    A panel that can display Web content. The panel provides a number of named properties that you can listen to for changes in order to observe the changes in the status of loading and displaying content.

    Methods that affect the Web content or the way it is displayed do not complete immediately, but instead queue the request for completion at some future time. Generally, requests will not have taken effect by the time the method returns. However, it is guaranteed that a sequence of requests will always be completed in the order that they are made.

    Requires JavaFX: This class cannot be instantiated unless JavaFX is available. See BundleInstaller.isFXRuntimeAvailable().

    Since:
    3.0
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Field Detail

      • HISTORY_PROPERTY

        public static final String HISTORY_PROPERTY
        A property that is updated when the history state changes. Listeners may use this as a cue to update whether "forward" and "back" type buttons should be enabled.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • LOAD_COMPLETED_PROPERTY

        public static final String LOAD_COMPLETED_PROPERTY
        A property that is updated when a page stops loading for any reason. The value of the property will be a member of the JWebPanel.LoadCompletionState enumeration.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • LOAD_EXCEPTION_PROPERTY

        public static final String LOAD_EXCEPTION_PROPERTY
        A property that is updated when an exception occurs while loading a page. The property change event will store the address that was loading as the old value, and the throwable that was triggered as the new value.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • LOAD_PROGRESS_PROPERTY

        public static final String LOAD_PROGRESS_PROPERTY
        A Number property that is updated with the current page loading progress. The property will be -1 if the progress is indeterminate. Otherwise, it will be a value between 0 and 100, inclusive.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
